However, the decor is aging somewhat and I expected something fresher.	Slightly tired decor, but clean and comfortable.	This decor (and that within the room) is not what one usually encounters in a 4-star hotel.	Also, the overall ambiance of this hotel is 'dark'.	The decor is best described as "confused".	From the outside, it's relatively plain, but once inside you immediately see that the decor is very modern and chic.	None of the interior seemed to be the same (wallpaper, chairs, curtains, etc but the bedding was the simple white).	Our 12th-floor standard double room had been remodeled but the furniture seemed low quality with knicks and scratches already marring surfaces.